    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Harmony Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page dashboard structure is used to provide a high-level overview first, followed by thematic, interactive sections. The user flow is guided by a sticky navigation bar, allowing non-linear exploration of the courses, development methodology, quality assurance process, and timeline. This structure was chosen over a linear report format to make the dense, process-oriented information more accessible and engaging for stakeholders who need to grasp key project metrics and stages quickly. Key interactions include course filtering, clickable process steps, and expandable deliverable details. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Project KPIs (Goal: Inform): Presented as large numbers for immediate impact. Method: HTML/Tailwind. Interaction: None. Justification: Provides a quick, scannable summary of the project's scale.
        - Course List (Goal: Organize/Inform): Presented as interactive cards with icons and expandable content structure. Method: HTML/Tailwind, JS for filtering and accordion toggle. Interaction: Filtering by category, clicking card to expand/collapse content. Justification: Allows users to easily browse, focus on specific course areas, and drill down into the academic content structure without navigating away.
        - Course Categories (Goal: Compare): A donut chart to show the distribution of courses. Method: Chart.js Canvas. Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: Visually summarizes the thematic balance of the curriculum.
        - Development Process (Goal: Change/Process): An interactive stepper diagram. Method: HTML/Tailwind, JS for click events. Interaction: Clicking a stage reveals details. Justification: Clearly visualizes the linear, multi-stage workflow in a more engaging way than a simple list.
        - Timeline (Goal: Change): A horizontal bar chart. Method: Chart.js Canvas. Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: Provides an intuitive visual representation of the project's schedule and phase durations.
        - Deliverables (Goal: Organize): An expandable accordion list. Method: HTML/Tailwind, JS for toggling. Interaction: Clicking to expand/collapse. Justification: Manages information density by hiding details until the user requests them.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
